This paper focuses on feedback control for locomotion, perception, and navigation of a bipedal robot. The use of virtual constraints and gait libraries is a common approach in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the implementation of a controller, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of algorithms for locomotion, perception, and navigation suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the mention of walking over different terrains and riding a Segway suggests the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for perception and navigation.
